Configure advanced job filtering for jobBot with language, location, work mode, and skills preferences.

## Configuration Options

Add these to your .env file to customize job filtering:

**LANGUAGE**
- Default: english
- Filter jobs by language (useful for job boards with mixed languages)

**PREFERRED_LOCATIONS** (comma-separated)
- Example: Pune, Mumbai, Bangalore
- Only jobs matching these locations will be sent
- Leave empty to accept all locations

**PREFERRED_WORK_MODES** (comma-separated)
- Options: remote, hybrid, office
- Example: remote,hybrid (sends remote and hybrid jobs, excluding office-only)
- Leave empty to accept all work modes

**PREFERRED_SKILLS** (comma-separated)
- Example: Python,React,Node.js,Java,Angular
- Only jobs mentioning these skills will be sent
- Leave empty to accept all skill requirements

## Notification Format

With these settings enabled, notifications now include:
- **Role:** Job title
- **Company:** Company name
- **Skills:** Required or preferred technical skills
- **Location:** Job location/city
- **Work Mode:** Remote, Hybrid, or Office
- **Source:** Where the job was found

## Example Notification

```
*Senior Python Developer*
Company: Tech Company Inc
Location: Bangalore
Skills: Python, Django, PostgreSQL, Docker
Work Mode: Remote
Source: Career Page
https://example.com/jobs/123
```
